ter-finals. The remainder head to the repechages  RUGBY SEVENSMen's semi-final (15:30):Team SA vs FranceMen's bronze (19:00):TBCMen's final (19:45):TBC  SKATEBOARDING (Postponed to Monday due to the weather)Men's street prelims:Brandon ValjaloMen's street final:Brandon Valjalo TBC  SURFINGMen's first round, heats (from 19:00):Jordy Smith and Matt McGillivrayWomen's first round, heats (from 23:48):Sarah Baum  SWIMMINGWomen's 100m butterfly, heats (11:08):Erin GallagherWomen's 100m butterfly, semi-finals (20:30):Erin Gallagher TBC  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2